content.detailedDescription:
Me and my band had just finished a live show when i felt a strong urge to go outside, standing on a fire-escape stairway. clear skies. as i was looking up to watch the stars i saw 6 bright orange triangles in formation, forming a perfect triangle themselves. they came from the se and headed nw, flying directly over me, making no sound but at high speed. i could clearly see how 3 of them split from the formation and headed ne making a very sharp turn at even higher speed. the remaining 3 continued their path nw, whilst 2 of the separated suddenly turned around and flew right over my head. i estimated them flying about 500 meters high. again, no sound. i went inside to get the rest of the band but nobody was willing to go outside, thinking i was fooling them. except for our soundguy. i told him i had seen ufo's without telling him what they looked like and as soon as we went outside and looked up, the remaining triangle who had separated to the ne came flying straight over us. he was stunned, like me. i asked him: what did you just see? and he confirmed it was a bright orange triangle. 
i totally expected reports next day in the papers as a lot of people were outside enjoying the great weather and the funfair in town, but nothing!
weeks later i found out they had been spotted in belgium by hundreds of witnesses and they even interrupted a live radio show because of the calls coming in.
although it was a clear sky, there was one cloud in the nw which helped me to determine their cruising height as the 3 triangles who maintained their path briefly disappeared behind it.
this is the first time i have reported this sighting because of the ridicule that followed the days after the event. even though i had a reliable witness !
content.summary: 6 triangles flying in a triangle-formation then splitting up in 3 and 3, making 90 degree turns

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were coming home on 96 highway just n. e. of carl junction, mo. which is just n. of joplin, mo. we approached the last cross road before our turn onto 171 highway,. between the side road on our s. and the 171 highway in front of us a mile down the road i noticed a very low set of lights. there were 2 white lights in front (that we're more like windows than lights because there was i beam from them) and the rest  on the object was red. i slowed down to a crawl and pointed it out to my husband asking him , " what is that " ? he said just glancing, " oh, it's just a tower." i replied, " that is not a tower, there is nothing under it!". he looked again and i pointed out that you could clearly see the lights of carl junction under with no obstruction. i rolled the window down and there was no noise coming from it at all. we went to the intersection and turned around. we got back where we were and it was completely gone. i drove down the side road to see if it had landed in the field it was hovering over and it had not. i have seen strange things in the sky before but, i have never ever seen anything like this before this close in my life. i didn't report this because i didn't know who to report it to and was unaware of the other sightings in the area at this time.
content.summary: S. of 96 highway approx. half mile s. of road. hovering over field. we turned around next driveway went back it was gone.

content.detailedDescription:
Approximately 4:55 am or 4:57 am sitting having coffee on my patio looking out at the backyard when i saw a medium-light green object in the distance falling....When i first saw it i stood up and moved to the right.

 the angle was close to 11:00 falling down to 3:30 /4:00 ...There was no tail as in a comet and it fell slow not like one would see a shooting star or meteor shower. 
i am about 1 to 1 1/2 miles from the large lake and it appeared to be over the lake falling downward towards the lake.

i saw the object only through the clearings of the trees, then there is a gap to the next tree and then i lost sight of it behind more trees...I believe my directional angle is close i only had my cell phone compass. i took a picture of the yard in order to show the descent if necessary.

i had/have no idea what it was. i will admit my heart skipped a beat and swallowed the coffee that lingered in my mouth...In other words i had a brief omg moment. after it left my sight i sat down and waited...Just in case it ascended or something. then i went to check the time which at that moment was 4:58 am...My first instinct was to call non-emergency police but that quickly faded. 
my feelings after the sighting?  wow! in wonderment
i made a mistake telling a neighbor...The look of foolishness on their faces made me delay contacting mufon or the ufo hunters; william birnes.
i felt since it was not a ufo shape and just a green round object it may be of no significance. but one never knows.
content.summary: Seemingly a solid light green round shaped object

content.detailedDescription:
Approx. 12:30am before going to bed on 14/oct/14 i stepped out side my house to look at the sky. fort lauderdale airport is about 6 miles south east of my house. i first thought the lights where an aircraft on climb out but then realized they werent aircraft lights and it wasnt moveing. it was a series of red and green lights that pulsed, flashed and stayed steady and was some sort of craft. during the nine years living in this house i know the sight and movements of airplanes and helocopters, blimps and clouds, this was nothing we have. it seemed to be looking for something in the way it moved and hovered. my girlfriend was asleep on the couch, i was reluctant to get her for fear of the thing leaving. after about 5 minutes however i did get her knowing she wouldnt believe what it was without seeing for herself. we watched it for another 3 or 4 minutes. it continued to move and hover and occasionally drop very low behind trees, i thought it was landing at the airport. through my binoculars i could make out a shape. after dropping one last time it didnt reapear, i assume it went out over the ocean. i was freaked out.The thing was big and close and didnt seem shy. i realized air traffic had stopped until it was gone, then take off and landings resumed. i was surprised there was no broward shriffs helocopter or maybe military aircraft. the airport control tower had to have seen it. 
    im just glad they didnt eat my brain.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Hovering and erratic flight over and around ftlauderdale airport

content.detailedDescription: I was on a gravel road by the railroad tracks at about 1 am in the last part of august in 2008. i saw many falling stars in the area while cat fishing. that night i got there about 1 am and got out of my truck to see the light of what i thought was a falling star brightening breaking apart and coming at my direction from the se and heading in a nw direction at about 500 feet above the ground. it came just above me and i saw that it was moving much to slow to be a falling star. it was 2 lights at this point and was separated by about 4 inches width from my perspective while just at 90 degrees above me. when it was just above me it disappeared and i was unable to regain sight of the object. the part that really made me pack up and leave was that the lights did not flash at all and the object made no noise. i was within 3000 feet of highway 3/46 and there was not even a car or truck in the area at the time to make any noise. completely silent even when the object(s) were within 500 feet. the lights were stationary in distance from each other as if it were one object and stayed in a straight path. very bright. but i was unable to see features of the object or objects that were the source of the lights.
content.summary: 2 bright white lights seemingly attached to each other moving se to nw

content.detailedDescription:
Shortly after turning onto rt13s from w trenton ave in my car, i observe 6-8(1 or 2 vanished) of these relatively small orbs in the sky at a rather low altitude.  rather mesmerized i unfortunately do not pull over and park to properly observe or get pics/video, but slow significantly and observe from the time of first notice, through passing under, and occasionally looking back(carefully!) after driving under.  one car on the opposite side of the road is parked with its hazards on and it could be assumed that the driver is observing, but i am too occupied with these orbs myself to see what they're doing.  as bright and relatively low as these were and at around 8:45 on a sat night, there were definitely other witnesses to this. 

starting from the first perspective before driving past, there are 3 orbs close to one another to the left which seem to hover and not move much.  there are a few more spread out moreso above the roadway that are more active in their movement, and 1 or 2 actually disappear from my sight.  these do not seem to move in any pattern or relation to one another, or make any sudden directional changes, but are moving in various directions(mostly up/down although i did observe one move sideways). the orbs themselves are all similar in size, bright reddish-orange, and flickering like a candle.

after passing by and under these, no strangeness in myself or my car was observed except awe.  i did however begin to develop the cold i'm currently suffering from about 24 hrs after observance, but of course any connection to the event is highly doubtful and i'm only adding for detail.

the observant will notice a report of a very similar occurrence a recently in this exact same spot, as well as other recent morrisville activity(the similar report and another recent m-ville sighting are both on saturdays as well i think).  bucks is a well known hotbed for activity after all and something may very well be happening in morrisville right now.  the only "rational" possibility i can see is if the farm is putting stuff up in the air but i highly doubt it.  i guess it could be done with floating objects of flickering light or something, but this would be hard to pull off and appear the way they did.  they were quite bright and the three to the left that seemed close together and stationary lend credence to a origin of, shall we say, strangeness.  regardless, i may e-mail the farm and inquire about this as well as to see if they observed this phenomena as well.
content.summary: Several flickering orbs of orange-red light slowly move about in the sky

content.detailedDescription: It was at lower waterfall at yellowstone national park at the view point from the above of waterfall. i did not noticed any movements until got back to home and start working with pictures. 5 different object, movements of 2 objects captured same time. object one: cylinder like shape was moving counterclockwise from the middle of mountain down, changing shape to shade like to boomerang with thick center, then at the bottom of the rock changed to humanoid like shade. object two: cylinder shape, same time appeared from the waterfall fog and start moving up and then straight towards mountain, then went down into the fog. object three: shade like, on one pic- on zoom like flying figure with head, torso, 2 legs and hands extended forward-then changed the shape like a trapeze with semi-lunar front part, got into the cave on the side of rock, then disappeared. object four and five: orb like were moving one above each other: one on the flat part of the rock and another close to wall of rock. i stop making pictures - which was done in continuing shooting mode, because i haven't seen the objects during the picturing.
content.summary: 3: one cigar, one shape, and one orb, different time, sme place

content.detailedDescription: At cvs in binghàmton waiting for my grandma with my grandpa listening to music and suddenly the came from the north east - east. i turned and out the car windows seen what i thought was my imagination playing tricks on me but what looked like floating balloon like objects with extremely bright lights they moved how a buoy would on water in a wobbly manner and the lights were a yellow -orange color for both objects.I thought they were like helicopters or planes but then me and my grandpa realized that airplanes and helicopters don't move like that plus they made absolutely no noise whatsoever. they first object was higher up and farther away and it moved straight up and changed directors quite a bit before just vanishing the second object was much closer and lower in altitude and did exactly the same that the first one did.I personally felt scared but at the same time in a state of awe because of the whole sight of both objects i then went to get a cellphone with a camcorder and camera setting to snap a picture or video but i was so shocked that i couldn't get a good chance to try to do so but if i could of i definitely without a doubt with no hesitation would of did so.After the sighting it remained in my memory on the whole trip back home and me and my grandpa told each other what did we just see.We finally lost the objects because they just vanished and faded into literally thin air?.

content.detailedDescription: Approximately 9:40 i was traveling north on us131. i saw what appeared to be a very bright star to the north. as i got closer, it was apparent this is not an aircraft i have ever seen. 1. no flashing lights. 2. row of 4 square intensely bright white lights close together in a row straight across. the free way curves around, but i was easily able to see it was not moving. i estimate altitude under 1 mile, approximately 1 mile east of us131 between sand lake and pierson exit. there is no military location, nor any item of significance to explain possible drone work, blimp etc. no outline was able to be seen due to foggy mist. lost view as object was on passenger side of vehicle. passenger was completely enthralled. claimed as we went past it at a range of maybe 1 mile, there was also an orange square window much dimmer. far too high to be a new tower, and there was plainly nothing under it. 2 adult eyewitnesses. lights appeared to be between 50 and 100 feet square.
content.summary: Fog  light rain, clouds. hovering object that is not of any known type

content.detailedDescription: I decided to take a trip to skyline drive to see if the leaves had begun to change color yet.  upon reaching the area there was really no significant change so i decided to be a little adventurous and take random roads off the beaten path. i had stopped first at a property that had been listed for sale and took a few pictures there because the view was really quite beautiful. i went down the road a ways and noticed longhorn cattle in the field and thought that was very unusual for this area so i decided to take pictures of them. it was really strange when i got out of the car one of the young cows started running towards me so i took his picture. i thought that was really odd because i grew up on a farm and i don't recall cows running towards me they are generally running away. i drove around for awhile then headed home. it wasn't until i was looking at my pictures that i noticed something unusual above a tree so i enlarged it. when i enlarged the photo on my i-pad i noticed additional objects for a lack of better words to describe it around the clouds. i didn't think they were birds due to the height of the object but i am certainly no expert. i am in hopes that you can tell me what i am seeing in these photos.
content.summary: I did not know they were in my pictures.

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were taking our dogs out to use the washroom. it was so clear we were standing and looking at the stars, my husband pointed out the big dipper. he then said what's that moving, it looked like something moving away from the dipper across the sky. it was bigger than the stars in the big dipper. it was a yellow orange color that glowed and it was round. it made no sound and it moved slowly across the sky. it moved to about the edge of the milky way and suddenly started appearing smaller and smaller suggesting to us that it had stopped and started traveling upwards and away from us. it was quickly gone to a pin size then completely gone from site. there was a plane traveling much higher than it and we could easily observe the differences between the two. i have 21 years canadian military airforce/navy and my husband was an emergency management coordinator. we both were left not knowing what we saw.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Round glowing object. sitting at tip of big dipper. started moving slowly across the sky. then shot up and disappear ed to a pin size then gone.

content.detailedDescription:
It was friday night and i was giving my friend a ride to town....I always look at the planes in the sky...We are close to scott afb... when i notice a red object in the air...I said to my friend..."that plane sure is moving awfully slow"....He agreed...As we got closer we both said.."that ain't no plane"...So i looked for a place to pull over....As soon as i pulled over the object moved...It started to descend....And transform from a red ball of light in to a structured object....Different color list blinking rapidly..Once it had transformed shapes it glided off in a westerly direction
picking up speed until we couldn't see it anymore...We were stunned , shocked and speechless...And i kept saying .."somebody else has to be see this"...I wanted to turn around and follow it but my friend didn't want to..I wasn't sure if i had got the pictures of it...Because it was transforming and moving ,,,but when i zoomed in on the pictures i got i was thrilled because i caught it while it was transforming and when it became a squared like structure....
content.summary: Saw what i thought was a very slow moving plane hovering over the old high school
